## Tenant ID Handling & Owner Cheat Code

### Tenant ID Generation

When a new business (tenant) signs up, the system automatically generates a unique tenant ID in the backend. Users should **not** be asked to enter a tenant ID during sign up. The backend creates the tenant, generates the tenant ID, and associates the new owner/admin user and all related data with that tenant. This ensures secure, isolated multi-tenant operation.

For invited users joining an existing business, the invitation flow (e.g., via email invite or token) securely links them to the correct tenant.

### Owner Cheat Code

For development or initial setup, you can use the "owner cheat code" to quickly create an owner/admin user and a new tenant for testing:

- If the system detects no tenants or users in the database, it may allow the first sign up to create both a tenant and an owner/admin user automatically (no tenant ID required).
- Alternatively, you can use a special environment variable or CLI command (see backend documentation or scripts) to bootstrap an owner/admin user and tenant for local development.

> **Note:** Never use the cheat code or initial owner setup in production after onboarding real tenants.

